Choose the best approximation of the

00:00:11.067 --> 00:00:14.898
United States population in 2014.

00:00:14.898 --> 00:00:16.941
So they say three times
10 to the eighth people

00:00:16.941 --> 00:00:18.767
or three times 10 to the ninth people.

00:00:18.767 --> 00:00:19.766
This is a big difference.

00:00:19.766 --> 00:00:20.775
This is a factor of 10.

00:00:20.775 --> 00:00:24.073
This is 10 times this right over here.

00:00:24.073 --> 00:00:25.651
So which one's closer?

00:00:25.651 --> 00:00:29.135
So if I were to round this to the nearest

00:00:29.135 --> 00:00:34.135
hundred million, this
would go to 300,000,000.

00:00:38.416 --> 00:00:42.173
300,000,000, this is
three times 100,000,000.

00:00:42.173 --> 00:00:44.912
This is the same thing as three times,

00:00:44.912 --> 00:00:49.637
three times 100,000,000.

00:00:49.637 --> 00:00:52.204
And 100,000,000 we see has eight zeros.

00:00:52.204 --> 00:00:55.593
So this is the same thing as
three times 10 to the eighth.

00:00:55.593 --> 00:00:58.115
Three times 10 to the eighth power,

00:00:58.115 --> 00:01:00.087
which they have right over here.

00:01:00.087 --> 00:01:01.000
Three times 10 to the ninth,

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:03.147
that would be 3,000,000,000.

00:01:03.147 --> 00:01:04.646
That would be almost 10 times

00:01:04.646 --> 00:01:05.945
as large as this.

00:01:05.945 --> 00:01:07.779
So we would definitely
wanna go with this one.

00:01:07.779 --> 00:01:08.987
Three times 10 to the eight people

00:01:08.987 --> 00:01:10.206
is a pretty good approximation.

00:01:10.206 --> 00:01:12.331
This is 300,000,000 people.

00:01:12.331 --> 00:01:15.454
So we're kind of rounding
to the nearest 100,000,000.

00:01:15.454 --> 00:01:18.008
In 2014, the population of the world

00:01:18.008 --> 00:01:23.008
was about 7,125,000,000 people.

00:01:23.355 --> 00:01:24.669
Choose the best approximation

00:01:24.669 --> 00:01:27.871
of the world population in 2014.

00:01:27.871 --> 00:01:28.951
Well here we're dealing with,

00:01:28.951 --> 00:01:30.275
this is billions here,

00:01:30.275 --> 00:01:32.504
so let me just round
to the nearest billion.

00:01:32.504 --> 00:01:36.025
So we could say this is
roughly 7,000,000,000.

00:01:37.751 --> 00:01:39.445
So approximately 7,000,000,000

00:01:39.445 --> 00:01:41.904
if we're rounding to the nearest billion.

00:01:42.984 --> 00:01:44.812
A billion is 10 to the ninth.

00:01:44.812 --> 00:01:47.262
We see we have nine zeros here.

00:01:47.262 --> 00:01:48.202
So this is going to be equal

00:01:48.202 --> 00:01:52.753
to seven times 10 to the ninth power.

00:01:52.753 --> 00:01:54.215
Which is this right over here.

00:01:54.215 --> 00:01:55.841
This would be 700,000,000.

00:01:55.841 --> 00:01:57.662
This is less than a 10th

00:01:57.662 --> 00:01:59.712
of the actual world population.

00:01:59.712 --> 00:02:01.291
This is 7,000,000,000,

00:02:01.291 --> 00:02:02.950
which is, if you're rounding
to the nearest billion,

00:02:02.950 --> 00:02:06.024
how many people there were in 2014.

00:02:06.376 --> 00:02:08.062
Approximately how many times larger

00:02:08.062 --> 00:02:10.012
was the world population,

00:02:10.012 --> 00:02:12.487
how many times larger
was the world population

00:02:12.487 --> 00:02:16.388
than the United States population in 2014?

00:02:16.388 --> 00:02:18.925
Well what was the world population?

