Once again, they're taking approximately.

00:02:21.003 --> 00:02:23.533
They're saying two, 20, 200.

00:02:23.533 --> 00:02:24.950
So if we're saying approximately,

00:02:24.950 --> 00:02:26.227
see the world population,

00:02:26.227 --> 00:02:27.912
if we're using the approximation,

00:02:27.912 --> 00:02:31.673
was seven times 10 to the ninth power,

00:02:31.673 --> 00:02:33.008
and the United States population,

00:02:33.008 --> 00:02:35.922
we said it was roughly, in 2014,

00:02:35.922 --> 00:02:37.755
three times 10 to the eighth.

00:02:37.755 --> 00:02:42.755
So we could divide the world population,

00:02:42.934 --> 00:02:45.039
or our approximation of
the world population,

00:02:45.039 --> 00:02:47.993
by our approximation of the
United States population.

00:02:47.993 --> 00:02:50.652
So our approximation
of the world population

00:02:50.652 --> 00:02:52.277
divided by the approximation

00:02:52.277 --> 00:02:53.960
of the United States population,

00:02:53.960 --> 00:02:56.758
three times 10 to the eight power,

00:02:56.758 --> 00:02:58.500
well what's that going to be?

00:02:58.500 --> 00:03:01.019
This is going to be approximately,

00:03:01.019 --> 00:03:04.653
well, this is actually
going to be exactly 7/3.

00:03:04.653 --> 00:03:08.214
So we could say seven divided by three,

00:03:08.214 --> 00:03:11.174
that's 7/3, times,

00:03:11.174 --> 00:03:12.950
what's 10 to the ninth

00:03:12.950 --> 00:03:15.678
divided by 10 to the eighth power?

00:03:15.678 --> 00:03:17.353
Well that's just going to be 10.

00:03:17.353 --> 00:03:20.580
10 to the ninth is 10
to the eighth times 10,

00:03:20.580 --> 00:03:21.973
and if we divide that by 10 to the eighth,

00:03:21.973 --> 00:03:23.761
we're just gonna be left with 10.

00:03:23.761 --> 00:03:25.292
Or, if we think about exponent properties,

00:03:25.292 --> 00:03:27.318
we have the same base, 10 to the ninth,

00:03:27.318 --> 00:03:29.037
divided by 10 to the eighth,

00:03:29.037 --> 00:03:31.033
